      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WARPARTY (2) resumed in stronger, beaten 1.5 lengths over 1200m at Ballarat. Was heavily bet, and the longer sprint suits. Has more up his sleeve, and Coffey replaces the 2kg apprentice. Best form puts him right in this. YOOMEE WONDER (5) is busting to win again and was good in town before her 1.4 lengths defeat over 1300m in a 70 at Cranbourne. Draws inside again, and John Allen goes aboard and has won on the mare. Faces an easier assignment and is a live chance. STRIKE GOLD (1) has been racing in better company and has jumped out since his distance Seymour placing 38 days ago. Finally draws an inside barrier and has the ability. Keep onside. KIJIVU (7) is free running and deserved his Maiden win at this track. Meech goes on SABERTOOTH (4), who presents third-up and showed enough two back on debut to say she'll win more races. Has two key gear additions and keep safe.",
